Google Chrome remains the most popular Internet browser, according to data from NetMarketShare for March 2018. Chrome is miles ahead in both the mobile and desktop market, with over 60% market share across both platforms. Safari is the main competitor to Chrome on mobile, with a market share of 26.30% – compared to Chrome’s market share of 65.12%. Internet Explorer is just ahead of Firefox for second place on desktop, with Microsoft Edge and Safari trailing behind them. The most popular Internet browsers across mobile and desktop for March 2018 are listed below.  